		"description": "<p><em><strong>Requirement:</strong> You must be wielding a weapon that deals piercing or slashing damage</em></p>\n<p>You slash at a creature&rsquo;s arteries, hoping to exsanguinate it. Spend 2 hit dice and make a melee weapon attack against a target within range. If you hit, the creature takes normal weapon damage and must make a Constitution saving throw. If it fails, it immediately suffers necrotic damage equal to half of its normal hit points or enough to drop it to 1 hit point remaining, whichever is less. A creature that succeeds on its saving throw is rattled until the end of its next turn. Creatures without blood are immune to this maneuver.</p>",
